@page "/enigma-game-mechanics"

<SeoHead Title="Enigma Game Mechanics | Rooms, Puzzles, Rewards, and Maps"
         Description="Read about Enigma's room structure, puzzle interactions, map discovery, Maze Nuggets, and the systems that drive the maze economy."
         OpenGraphType="article"
         SchemaType="Article"
         Keywords="Enigma mechanics, room puzzles, Maze Nuggets, map discovery, puzzle systems" />

<div class="content seo-page-shell">
    <section class="panel seo-page-hero">
        <span class="profile-kicker">Mechanics</span>
        <h1>Enigma Game Mechanics</h1>
        <p>Enigma is built around rooms, puzzle states, map ownership, and persistent player progress. The game systems are simple at the input level but layered at the run and economy level.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Room Structure</h2>
        <h3>Start, Reward, and Finish Rooms</h3>
        <p>Every maze includes a start room, a finish room, and standard or reward rooms in between. Doors and walls are driven by the seed layout.</p>
        <h3>In-Room Interaction</h3>
        <p>Players move directly inside the room surface. Puzzle consoles appear only for puzzles that need an overlay or precise focused interaction.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Puzzle Structure</h2>
        <h3>Stage Puzzles</h3>
        <p>Pressure plates, zone puzzles, and other spatial interactions can resolve directly on the stage.</p>
        <h3>Overlay Puzzles</h3>
        <p>Memory, logic, timing, and route puzzles can open through the room console, keeping the game focused on the room rather than a separate page.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Map and Economy Systems</h2>
        <h3>Discovery</h3>
        <p>Discovery belongs to the player who actually completed or founded the map. Ownership transfer does not create discovery.</p>
        <h3>Ownership</h3>
        <p>Maps can be owned, listed, sold, recycled to the bank, and tracked through marketplace history.</p>
    </section>
</div>
